'''Dempster Brothers, Inc.''' of [[Knoxville, Tennessee]], was an industrial firm that made [[waste collection vehicle|waste handling vehicles]] including  the '''Dempster Dumpmaster''' and '''Dempster Dinosaur'''. The firm was originally established by [[George Roby Dempster]] with his brothers Thomas and John Dempster.

==Dempster Dumpmaster==
The Dempster Dumpmaster, introduced in the 1950s,<ref>{{Cite web|url = http://www.tigerdude.com/garbage/frontload/index.html|title = Front-End Loaders|accessdate = 2014-12-30|website = History of refuse collection (or the garbage truck)|publisher = tigerdude.com}}</ref> was the first commercially successful, front-loading [[garbage truck]] in the United States. The product uses the ''Dempster-Dumpster'' system of mechanically emptying standardized metal containers, which had been patented by the company in 1937. It had arms at the front that picked up a [[dumpster]] and lifted it over the cab to tip it into the hopper. A rearward-traveling compacting panel compressed the garbage stored in the truck, and was also used to push it out through a door at the back when it was being emptied.

