{{Nihongo|'''Kawagoe Power Station'''|川越火力発電所|Kawagoe karyokuhatsudensho}} is a large [[natural gas|gas-fired]] power station in [[Kawagoe, Mie]], [[Japan]]. The facility operates at an installed capacity of 4,802&nbsp;[[Megawatt|MW]], making it the largest power station of its kind.<ref>[http://www.chuden.co.jp/english/investor/ir/pdf/datasheets_en.pdf Energy in Japan]{{dead link|date=December 2017 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.chubu.meti.go.jp/sangyokanko/tokai_monozukuri1710web/en/mie_5_1.htm# |title=Kawagoe Electric Power Museum |access-date=2010-02-12 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100829080157/http://www.chubu.meti.go.jp/sangyokanko/tokai_monozukuri1710web/en/mie_5_1.htm# |archive-date=2010-08-29 |dead-url=yes |df= }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.industcards.com/top-100-pt-1.htm# |title=Top 100 largest power stations |access-date=2010-02-12 |archive-url=https://wayback.archive-it.org/all/20121006110626/http://www.industcards.com/top-100-pt-1.htm# |archive-date=2012-10-06 |dead-url=yes |df= }}</ref>
