'''''On the Line''''' is a 2011 Canadian documentary by [[Frank Wolf (filmmaker)|Frank Wolf]] that investigates the risks and consequences associated with the proposed [[Enbridge Northern Gateway Pipelines]] project. The film is set in the context of a 2,400&nbsp;km biking, hiking, rafting and kayaking journey that two friends embark on from the Alberta oil sands to the British Columbia coast. As the pair travel the proposed pipeline route, they encounter a broad cross-section of people who voice their perspective on the issues associated with the project. It won the 'Spirit of Action Prize' at the 2012 Santa Cruz Film Festival<ref>{{cite web|title=On The Line at SCFF|url=http://santacruz.festivalgenius.com/2012/films/ontheline_frankwolf_santacruz2012}}</ref> and was chosen for the VIFF Selects section at the 2011 [[Vancouver International Film Festival]]. It airs on CBC's [[documentary (TV channel)]] in Canada multiple times through 2015.<ref>{{cite web|title=On The Line on CBC's documentary channel|url=http://www.cbc.ca/programguide/program/on_the_line/}}</ref> The film features music by Peirson Ross, [[Terry Jacks]], [[Chilliwack (band)|Chilliwack]], Kola Collective, Phontaine,Tessa Amy, and Eric Stanger. ==References== {{reflist}}
