{{Infobox dam | name = Silvan Dam | image = | image_caption = | name_official = Silvan Barajı | dam_crosses = [[Batman River]] | location = [[Silvan, Turkey]] | dam_type = Embankment, [[concrete-face rock-fill]] | dam_length ={{Convert|440|m|ft|0|abbr=on}} | dam_height ={{Convert|174.5|m|ft|0|abbr=on}} | dam_elevation_crest = | dam_width_crest = | dam_width_base = | dam_volume ={{Convert|8500000|m3|acre.ft|0|abbr=on}} | spillway_type = | spillway_capacity = | purpose = Irrigation, power | status = UC | construction_began = 2011 | opening = 2019 est. | cost = | owner = [[State Hydraulic Works]] | res_name = Silvan Reservoir | res_capacity_total = {{Convert|7300000000|m3|acre.ft|abbr=on}} | res_capacity_active = | res_capacity_inactive= | res_elevation = | res_max_length = | res_surface = {{Convert|178|km2|mi2}} | res_catchment = | res_max_depth = | plant_operator = | plant_commission = 2017 est. | plant_turbines = 4 x 40 MW [[Francis-type]] | plant_capacity = 160 MW | plant_annual_gen = | plant_decommission = | location_map =Turkey | location_map_caption = | coordinates = {{coord|38|17|28.47|N|41|01|24.84|E|type:landmark|display=inline,title}} | website = | extra = }}
'''Silvan Dam''' is an embankment [[concrete-face rock-fill]] currently under construction on the [[Batman River]] in the district of [[Silvan, Turkey|Silvan]], [[Diyarbakır Province]] in southeastern [[Turkey]]. It is part of the [[Southeastern Anatolia Project]] and located upstream of the [[Batman Dam]]. Construction began on 26 July 2011 and is expected to be complete in 2017. The purpose of the dam is [[hydroelectric]] power production and irrigation. It is designed to irrigate an area of {{Convert|245000|ha|acre|abbr=on}}. The power station will have an installed capacity of 160 MW.<ref>{{cite web|title=Initiated the construction of the dam is SİLVAN|url=http://www.gap.gov.tr/gap-tan/haberler/silvan-barajinin-yapimina-baslandi|accessdate=21 May 2013|language=Turkish|publisher=GAP}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Silvan Dam Due Date Moved Up|url=http://www.ilkehaberajansi.com.tr/haber/silvan-barajinin-bitis-tarihi-one-alindi.html|publisher=Ilke Haber Ajansi|accessdate=21 May 2013|language=Turkish|date=4 April 2013}}</ref>
In 2014, the dam, as well as other in southeast Turkey such as the [[Ilisu Dam]], became a prime target of [[Kurdistan Workers' Party]] (PKK) militants after peace talks collapsed with the government. Attacks on the dam, supporting structures and workers are part of the PKK's efforts to stop construction. Construction of the dam was suspended temporarily late in the year.<ref>{{cite news|title=Turkey's Biggest Dam Project Victim of Faltering Peace|url=https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2014-11-12/turkey-s-biggest-dam-project-victim-of-faltering-peace|accessdate=25 November 2015|publisher=Bloomberg Business|date=12 November 2014}}</ref>
The dam is expected to be completed in 2019.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.hilalhaber.com/silvan-baraji-terore-inat-yukseliyor_d50105.html|title=Silvan Barajı teröre inat yükseliyor!|work=hilal Haber|language=Turkish|date=28 March 2017}}</ref>
