'''Tetradecylthioacetic acid''' ('''TTA''') is a [[chemical synthesis|synthetic]] [[fatty acid]] used as a nutritional supplement.

TTA acts as a [[peroxisome proliferator-activated receptor alpha]] (PPARα) [[agonist]] and increases mitochondrial fatty acid oxidation ''[[in vitro]]''.<ref name="Pmid">{{cite journal | pmid = 19267708 | year = 2009 | last1 = Løvås | first1 = K | last2 = Røst | first2 = TH | last3 = Skorve | first3 = J | last4 = Ulvik | first4 = RJ | last5 = Gudbrandsen | first5 = OA | last6 = Bohov | first6 = P | last7 = Wensaas | first7 = AJ | last8 = Rustan | first8 = AC | last9 = Berge | first9 = RK | last10 = Husebye | first10 = E. S. | title = Tetradecylthioacetic acid attenuates dyslipidaemia in male patients with type 2 diabetes mellitus, possibly by dual PPAR-alpha/delta activation and increased mitochondrial fatty acid oxidation | volume = 11 | issue = 4 | pages = 304–14 | doi = 10.1111/j.1463-1326.2008.00958.x | journal = Diabetes, obesity & metabolism| display-authors = 8 }}</ref>  In [[animal testing on rodents|rodent studies]], TTA has been reported to have other activities such as reducing inflammation<ref>{{cite journal | pmid = 22855292 | year = 2012 | last1 = Bjørndal | first1 = B | last2 = Grimstad | first2 = T | last3 = Cacabelos | first3 = D | last4 = Nylund | first4 = K | last5 = Aasprong | first5 = OG | last6 = Omdal | first6 = R | last7 = Portero-Otin | first7 = M | last8 = Pamplona | first8 = R | last9 = Lied | first9 = GA | last10 = Hausken | first10 = Trygve | last11 = Berge | first11 = Rolf K. | title = Tetradecylthioacetic Acid Attenuates Inflammation and Has Antioxidative Potential During Experimental Colitis in Rats | doi = 10.1007/s10620-012-2321-2 | journal = Digestive Diseases and Sciences| volume = 58 | pages = 97–106 | issue=1}}</ref> and preventing high fat diet induced adiposity and insulin resistance.<ref>{{cite journal | pmid = 11971945 | year = 2002 | last1 = Madsen | first1 = L | last2 = Guerre-Millo | first2 = M | last3 = Flindt | first3 = EN | last4 = Berge | first4 = K | last5 = Tronstad | first5 = KJ | last6 = Bergene | first6 = E | last7 = Sebokova | first7 = E | last8 = Rustan | first8 = AC | last9 = Jensen | first9 = J | last10 = Mandrup | first10 = S | last11 = Kristiansen | first11 = K | last12 = Klimes | first12 = I | last13 = Staels | first13 = B | last14 = Berge | first14 = R. K. | title = Tetradecylthioacetic acid prevents high fat diet induced adiposity and insulin resistance | volume = 43 | issue = 5 | pages = 742–50 | journal = Journal of Lipid Research| display-authors = 8 }}</ref>

In human clinical study, there have been mixed observations in preliminary studies.  One [[Phase I clinical trial|Phase I]] study showed no significant changes in the blood lipids or free fatty acids<ref>{{cite journal | pmid = 18427285 | year = 2008 | last1 = Pettersen | first1 = RJ | last2 = Salem | first2 = M | last3 = Skorve | first3 = J | last4 = Ulvik | first4 = RJ | last5 = Berge | first5 = RK | last6 = Nordrehaug | first6 = JE | title = Pharmacology and safety of tetradecylthioacetic acid (TTA): Phase-1 study | volume = 51 | issue = 4 | pages = 410–7 | doi = 10.1097/FJC.0b013e3181673be0 | journal = Journal of cardiovascular pharmacology}}</ref> and another showed that TTA attenuates [[dyslipidemia]] in patients with [[type 2 diabetes mellitus]].<ref name="Pmid" />

